'''Elizabeth Anna Halcyon "Beth" Littleford'''<ref name="filmr"/> (born July 17, 1968) is an American actress, [[comedienne]], and [[television personality]]. She is perhaps best known for being one of the original correspondents on the popular [[Comedy Central]] satirical news series ''[[The Daily Show]]'' from 1996 to 2000; she is also known as Tripp's mother Beth Campbell from ''[[I'm in the Band]]'' and Avery's mother, Ellen Jennings in ''[[Dog with a Blog]]''.

==Personal life==
Littleford was born in Nashville, the daughter of Jackie, a professor, and Philip O. Littleford, a cardiologist and inventor. She grew up in Winter Park, Florida.<ref name="filmr">[http://www.filmreference.com/film/23/Beth-Littleford.html Beth Littleford Biography (1968-)<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> She lives in [[Los Angeles, California]] with her husband, producer and director Rob Fox. Littleford and Fox have one son, Jackson Oliver Fox, born on July 30, 2005. The couple adopted a daughter, Halcyon ‘Hallie’ Juna, who was born on March 23, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://celebritybabies.people.com/2012/03/24/beth-littleford-welcomes-daughter-halcyon-juna/| title=Beth Littleford Welcomes Daughter Halcyon Juna| publisher=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=March 24, 2012| accessdate= March 24, 2012}}</ref>

==Career==
Littleford guest-starred on numerous television programs during the late 1990s and 2000s such as ''[[Spin City]]'' (where she had a multi-year occasional role), ''[[The West Wing (TV series)|The West Wing]]'', ''[[Family Guy]]'', and ''[[Frasier]]''. Littleford was also a celebrity commentator on [[VH1]]'s ''[[I Love the 80s Strikes Back]]'' in 2003, ''[[I Love the '90s (U.S. TV series)|I Love the 90s]]'' in 2004, ''[[I Love the 90s: Part Deux]]'' in 2005, ''[[I Love the New Millennium]]'' and ''The Great Debate'' in 2009.  She was the female lead on the short-lived [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] series ''[[Method and Red]]'', and also starred as [[Ben Tennyson]]'s mother Sandra in ''[[Ben 10: Race Against Time]]'', and reprised the role in the ''[[Ben 10: Alien Force]]'' episode 20 and again in ''[[Ben 10: Ultimate Alien]]''.  More recently, Littleford appeared in TV commercials for [[Laughing Cow]] cheese and a hotel chain. She starred in the [[Disney XD]] original show ''[[I'm in the Band]]'', the 2010 Disney channel movie ''[[Starstruck (2010 film)|Starstruck]]'', and played Suzanne Berger on [[MTV]]'s ''[[The Hard Times of RJ Berger]]'' and Dana on [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]'s ''[[Desperate Housewives]]''.
She also plays the Cascade Kitchen Counselor on the TV commercials (2012). She currently has a starring role in the [[Disney Channel]] original series ''[[Dog with a Blog]]''.

